<F P=100> CROATIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   RSK Asks Serbs Abroad To Prevent Air Strikes </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1602155694 Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service in 
Serbo-Croatian 1447 GMT 16 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1602155694 </F>
<F P=104>  Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Serbo-Croatian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpts] Knin, 16 Feb (TANJUG) -- The ministry of foreign 
affairs of the republic of Serb Krajina [RSK] called on all 
Serbs and Serb associations in the world today to do everything 
they can against the planned NATO air strikes on Serb military 
targets and the population of the Srpska republic, ISKRA 
reported. 
  "The casualty toll will be huge, whole families will perish, 
including infants. It will be a real genocide -- a crime which 
began in World War II when the Muslims and Croats, sponsored by 
Adolf Hitler, killed 1.5 million Serbs," the statement says. 
[passage omitted] 
  For their part, the Serbs have already done a great deal for 
establishing peace: They surrendered Sarajevo airport to 
UNPROFOR, they surrendered territories to the Muslims in 
exchange for peace on two occasions, and they saved 80,000 
Croats from being massacred by the Muslims. The Serbs have 
never besieged the city of Sarajevo. Sarajevo is a city divided 
into Serb and Muslim parts, ISKRA reports. 
  The ministry of foreign affairs calls on all Serbs in the 
world to present these details to politicians, parties, members 
of parliaments, journalists and other respected personalities, 
also calling for organization of protests because Serbs 
currently have no other weapons, the statement says. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

