<F P=100> CROATIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Tudjman on Croatia's Efforts To End Crisis </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1602234294 Zagreb Radio Croatia Network in Serbo-Croatian 
2300 GMT 16 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1602234294 </F>
<F P=104>  Zagreb Radio Croatia Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Serbo-Croatian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Croatian President Dr. Franjo Tudjman received 
Italian Senator Francesco Cossiga, who was paying a private 
unofficial visit, in the Presidential Palace this evening. 
  During the course of their friendly and open talks, 
President 
Tudjman and Senator Cossiga discussed the political situation in 
Croatia and developments in Bosnia-Herzegovina. President 
Tudjman informed his guest about efforts being invested by the 
Croatian state leadership aimed at ending the crisis in 
Bosnia-Herzegovina through political negotiations, i.e., in a 
peaceful way, to the benefit of all three nations living in that 
republic. 

</TEXT>

