<H3> <TI>   Extends Stay in Belgrade </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1602172894 Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service in 
Serbo-Croatian 1647 GMT 16 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1602172894 </F>
<F P=104>  Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Serbo-Croatian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpt] Belgrade, 16 Feb (TANJUG) -- Russian Deputy 
Foreign Minister Vitaliy Churkin, who arrived today on a suprise 
visit to Belgrade where he met Serbian President Slobodan 
Milosevic, will extend his stay in the Yugoslav capital by 
another day, TANJUG has learned from the office of the Russian 
NOVOSTI news agency in Belgrade. 
  The same source disclosed that Churkin's latest visit to 
Belgrade is directly linked to the situation in Sarajevo -- the 
NATO ultimatum -- and threats that Serb positions around that 
city will be attacked if the artillery is not withdrawn to a 
distance of 20 km from Sarajevo. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

