<F P=100> YUGOSLAVIA </F>
<F P=101> Serbia </F>
<H3> <TI>   To Meet With Karadzic </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU1702113894 Paris AFP in English 1052 GMT 17 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU1702113894 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris AFP </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Belgrade, Feb 17 (AFP) -- Russian special envoy 
Vitaliy Churkin is to have talks with Bosnian Serb leader 
Radovan Karadzic on Thursday, the Bosnian Serb news agency SRNA 
announced. 
  The meeting has been scheduled for after noon (1100 GMT) at 
the Bosnian Serb stronghold of Pale, east of Sarajevo. 
  Churkin has been on a special mission for Russian President 
Boris Yeltsin since Saturday to mediate in the Bosnian conflict. 
  He met twice with Serbia's ultranationalist President 
Slobodan Milosevic. 
  A third meeting was scheduled for later Thursday. 

</TEXT>

