<H3> <TI>   Emergency Government Session Called </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU1602171694 Paris AFP in English 1706 GMT 16 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU1602171694 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris AFP </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Skopje, Feb 16 (AFP) -- The Macedonian government 
met in emergency session Wednesday [16 February] following 
Greece's decision to close its northern port of Salonika to 
Macedonian goods and close its consulate general in Skopje. 
Macedonian commentators warned that the Greek move would cause 
regional destabilisation. 
  Greek Prime Minister Andreas Papandreou said Wednesday he 
was 
"forced" to take these steps because of what he called 
landlocked Macedonia's "continual provocations and growing 
irredentist intransigence." 
  Greece accuses the former Yugoslav republic of trying to 
usurp a name Athens says is solely part of Greek heritage and of 
harboring expansionist aims over the Greek province of the same 
name. 

</TEXT>

