<F P=100> MACEDONIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Commission Adopts Bill on Intelligence Agency </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU1602211494 Skopje MIC in English 16 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU1602211494 </F>
<F P=104>  Skopje MIC </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Unattributed report: "Legislative Commission: Intelligence </F>
Under Control"] 
  [Text] The defining of the responsibility of the director 
of the Intelligence Agency was the most controversial issue at 
yesterday's session of the parliament's Legislative Commission. 
At the end, the Commission adopted the proposal for a law for 
the forming of an Intelligence Agency. 
  The representatives of the Interior Ministry pointed out 
that 
the law defines the control at three levels: "The president of 
the state appoints and dismisses the director, the government 
can demand responsibility from the director for the activities 
of the Agency, and there will also be parliamentary supervision." 
  A couple of members of the commission emphasized the 
conceptual inconsistency that the director answers to organs 
which did not elect him. To this, the Interior Ministry 
representatives replied that the strengthened control is 
introduced in order to prevent the autonomous activities of the 
agency, but also not to allow involvement in the daily political 
interests. 
  In relation to this law, also two amendments were submitted. 
The first one specifies that the employees in the agency cannot 
carry out other activities and functions, and the second, that 
both the employees in the agency and the Interior Ministry have 
the right a 30 percent increase. 

</TEXT>

