<F P=101> Bulgaria </F>
<H3> <TI>   Air Force Command Denies Charge </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU1702085694 Sofia BTA in English 2149 GMT 16 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU1702085694 </F>
<F P=104>  Sofia BTA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Sofia, February 16 (BTA) -- Neither U.S. nor NATO 
aircraft are being refuelled in Bulgaria, the Bulgarian Air 
Force Command stated through the Press Office of the Ministry of 
Defence in response to reports in today's press. 
  The independent KONTINENT daily wrote today that "in the 
dead 
of the night, between 2 and 4 AM, NATO aircraft are refuelled at 
Sofia Airport." According to the report, inhabitants of 
residential districts close to the airport said that "in the 
past two weeks the roar of turboprop engines has become 
unbearable," thus confirming the information of an unnamed 
source. 

</TEXT>

