<F P=101> Bulgaria </F>
<H3> <TI>   Germany's Suessmuth Justifies NATO Ultimatum </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU1602130494 Sofia BTA in English 1148 GMT 16 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU1602130494 </F>
<F P=104>  Sofia BTA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Sofia, February 16 (BTA) -- This morning Prof. Dr. 
Rita Suessmuth, president of the German Bundestag, had a meeting 
with President Zhelyu Zhelev. She arrived here yesterday [15 
February] to receive the doctor honoris causa degree of the St. 
St. Cyril and Methodius University of Veliko Turnovo 
(northcentral Bulgaria). 
  We considered the problem of former Yugoslavia sharing the 
opinion that NATO's ultimatum is absolutely necessary because 
the bloodshed there must be stopped and because it is high time 
that the international community prove it can really do 
something to save the civil population, Prof. Suessmuth told 
reporters at the Sofia Airport before her departure. 
  Prof. Suessmuth and Dr. Zhelev discussed Bulgarian-German 
relations. After the meeting President Zhelev told reporters 
that Germany's economic presence in Bulgaria should be felt 
stronger. Germany can do this using the potential of its large 
companies, Dr. Zhelev said. Bulgaria's hope was expressed at 
the meeting that Germany would show understanding for its wish 
to conclude a debt settlement agreement with the London Club the 
soonest possible. 
  Meeting yesterday, Bundestag President Rita Suessmuth and 
National Assembly Chairman Aleksandur Yordanov considered the 
situation in ex-Yugoslavia and the possibilities of expanding 
German investments in Bulgaria. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

