<H3> <TI>   Greek General Arrives To Discuss Cooperation </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU1502133294 Sofia BTA in English 1252 GMT 15 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU1502133294 </F>
<F P=104>  Sofia BTA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Sofia, February 15 (BTA) -- The purpose of my visit 
here is to discuss bilateral military cooperation issues of 
mutual interest with Army General Lyuben Petrov, chief of the 
General Staff of the Bulgarian Army, said Admiral Khristos 
Limberis, chief of the General Staff of the National Defence of 
Greece, upon [name as received] his arrival here today. This is 
Admiral Limberis' first visit to Bulgaria in implementation of 
the Military Cooperation Plan between the two countries. 
  According to General Petrov, apart from military cooperation 
issues, the two sides will also discuss the Partnership for 
Peace initiative and Bulgaria's accession to it, as well as some 
aspects of the situation in the Balkans. Today the guest will 
be received by Defence Minister Valentin Aleksandrov and later 
by the Chief of the Parliamentary National Security Committee 
Nikolay Slatinski. 

</TEXT>

