<F P=101> Romania </F>
<H3> <TI>   Miners Strike Causes `Critical' Situation </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU1602212194 Bucharest ROMPRES in English 1845 GMT 16 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU1602212194 </F>
<F P=104>  Bucharest ROMPRES </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Bucharest, ROMPRES, 16/2/1994 -- The 24 unions 
composing the "Lignitul" Mining Unions Federation continued the 
general strike Wednesday, February 16. Vasile Chirculescu, 
deputy director-general of the Targu-Jiu Autonomous Public 
corporation told a ROMPRES coresspondent that in each of the 
three days of strike 100,000 tonnes of lignite and brown coal 
were extracted in each of the three coal field whose miners are 
on strike. The quantities sent to power stations during the 
strike stood at more than 90 percent of those supplied before 
the strike started. "The strike is not legal," said Chirculescu, 
"that's why we filed a lawsuit against the strikers' leaders and 
asked that the case be considered an emergency. The public 
corporation does not have enough money to solve the strikers' 
claims." 
  Coal power stations had around 2.4 million tonnes of coal in 
store Wednesday, February 16. The situation was critical at the 
stations Oradea 1 and 2, Suceava, Iasi and Arad, to which 
additional amounts of coal were sent. 

</TEXT>

