<H3> <TI>   Kovac, Moravcik Expelled From HZDS </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU1502202994 Prague CTK in English 1646 GMT 15 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU1502202994 </F>
<F P=104>  Prague CTK </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpts] Bratislava, Feb 15 (CTK) -- Slovak Deputy 
Premier Roman Kovac and Foreign Minister Jozef Moravcik have 
been expelled from the governing Movement for a Democratic 
Slovakia (HZDS), HZDS Spokeswoman Ivana Salczerova confirmed to 
CTK today. [passage omitted] 
  Salczerova said she did not believe that the nine HZDS 
deputies who supported the Alternative of Political Realism 
established by Roman Kovac and Moravcik would be also expelled 
from the ruling movement. On February 12, the HZDS Presidium 
give local party leadership the task of conducting talks with 
the deputies who had supported the alternative on their attitude 
to the program of the HZDS. "The approach is quite different as 
far as deputies are concerned," she said. 
  Three HZDS deputies -- Maria Vrablova, Jan Durana, and Ivan 
Jaros -- according to their own statement -- resigned their 
party functions in the leadership of the HZDS branch in Zilina, 
central Slovakia. 
  According to unconfirmed information one more HZDS deputy, 
Vladimir Bajan, has also resigned. 

</TEXT>

