<H3> <TI>   Opposition Fails To Set Nov Date </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU1702141294 Prague CTK in English 1155 GMT 17 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU1702141294 </F>
<F P=104>  Prague CTK </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Bratislava, Feb 17 (CTK) -- The constitutional bill 
of the Slovak opposition to hold early elections in November did 
not get the necessary three-fifths (90) of the votes in 
parliament today. 
  As a result, the date will be decided by referendum. A 
petition with at least 350,000 signatures is necessary to call a 
referendum. Premier Vladimir Meciar said he was ready to start 
collecting the signatures starting Monday [21 February]. 
  83 of 147 present deputies voted for the bill, while 49 were 
against and 15 abstained. 

</TEXT>

