<H3> <TI>   Rugova Unveils Project for Independent Kosovo </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU1502211494 Tirana ATA in English 1126 GMT 15 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU1502211494 </F>
<F P=104>  Tirana ATA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Tirana, February 15 (ATA) -- The president of the 
Republic of Kosova, Mr. Ibrahim Rugova, met on February 14 in 
Prishtina with Dr. Michael Venincer, the charge d'affaires of 
the Embassy in Belgrade, and Mr. Hejsek Joseph, the charge 
d'affaires of the Embassy of Czechia. President Rugova informed 
the diplomats about the present situation in Kosova, which is 
aggravated as a result of the everyday repression. Mr. Rugova 
spoke also on the harsh economical and social situation there. 
  Mr. Rugova presented to the Austrian and diplomats the 
political project for an independent and neutral Kosova as a 
more optimal solution. He stressed the necessity of an 
international protectorate for Kosova as a transitory phase 
which will make possible the normalization of life and will 
create the necessary conditions for negotiations. 

</TEXT>

