<H3> <TI>   Serb Court Continues Trials of Ethnic Albanians </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU1502181894 Tirana ATA in English 1119 GMT 15 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU1502181894 </F>
<F P=104>  Tirana ATA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Prishtina, February 15 (ATA) -- A staged process 
against Mr. Rustem Demaj, from Vrelle of Istog in Kosova, 
concluded in the Serbian Court of the region of Peje. Mr. 
Demaj, a captain in rest, was sentenced with five years in 
prison accused for jeopardizing of the territorial integrity. 
The defendant didn't accepted the accuse on the whole. 
  The Serbian Court of Peje began on February 14, the judgment 
of ten Albanians being under the charge of lesion of the 
territorial integrity of the so-called Yugoslavia. Three of the 
defendants, Mr. Myrteza Nura, writer, and Mr. Naser Zeka and 
Mazllum Kumanova, who were investigated, refuted the accuse on 
the whole. 
  At the same time, the Serbian Court of Prishtina went on 
with 
the judgment of nineteen Albanians, which has began since a year 
ago. 

</TEXT>

