<H3> <TI>   Yugoslavs Refuse Entry Visas to Helsinki Mission </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU1302210694 Tirana ATA in English 1116 GMT 13 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU1302210694 </F>
<F P=104>  Tirana ATA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Tirana, February 13 (ATA) -- The rump Yugoslavia's 
authorities refused to give visas for Kosova to a delegation for 
human rights of the Helsinki Federation, the Kosova Information 
Centre reported. 
  The delegation intended to observe what has happened to the 
Albanians returned from Austria, Scandinavian countries and 
Germany. 
  Concerning the refusal of the Serbian authorities to go to 
Kosova, Ms. Christine von Kohl told BBC: "This time we received 
no answer." She explained how she had personally talked with 
the official in charge of so-called Yugoslav Embassy in Vienna. 
  Ms. von Kohl said one of the reasons for refusing the visas 
might be the fact that the Belgrade's authorities want to show 
they do not observe the CSCE norms as it recently happened with 
the Amnesty International. 

</TEXT>

