<H3> <TI>   Zhelev Receives Rakovski Officer Legion Group </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU1702164094 Sofia Khorizont Radio Network in Bulgarian 1600 
GMT 17 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU1702164094 </F>
<F P=104>  Sofia Khorizont Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Bulgarian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] On 17 February President Zhelyu Zhelev received 
representatives of the Rakovski Bulgarian Officer Legion, who 
conveyed to him alarming details related to the financial 
situation of the Armed Forces. They demanded transparency and 
openness in reporting the budgets of the Army and the Ministry 
of Interior and insisted on decreasing the apparatus of the 
General Staff and the Ministry of Defense. The issue of 
restricting certain civil rights of the military in the Defense 
and Armed Forces Bill, which was adopted at the first reading, 
was addressed. 
  Those issues, President Zhelev said, will be placed on the 
agenda of the first meeting of the Consultative Council on 
National Security. 

</TEXT>

