<F P=100> ROMANIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   `Seriously Injured' in Car Accident </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU1702200394 Bucharest TINERETUL LIBER in Romanian 15 Feb 94 
p 1 </F>

<F P=103> AU1702200394 </F>
<F P=104>  Bucharest TINERETUL LIBER </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Romanian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Liana Buligan item: "Liviu Luca, Vice President of the </F>
National Confederation of Romania's Free Trade Unions Fratia, 
Has Had a Serious Accident Following His Statements for Our 
Paper!"] 
  [Text] On Thursday evening, 11 February, Mr. Liviu Luca, 
vice president of the National Confederation of Romania's Free 
Trade Unions [CNSLR] Fratia, granted an exclusive interview to 
our newspaper by making serious accusations against the current 
government. Only two days later, a car accident occurred in 
which Liviu Luca was seriously injured, while the "offender," 
SRI [Romanian Intelligence Service] Lieutenant Colonel Ion 
Buica, died. Although the interview, which was granted 
confidentially in Mr. Luca's office, was published only on 
Monday, 14 February 1994, by TINERETUL LIBER, we ask ourselves 
to what extent his bold statements and the accident that was 
caused by a SRI officer were just an ordinary coincidence. 

</TEXT>

