<F P=100> BOSNIA-HERZEGOVINA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Continued Serbian Aggression Around Bihac </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU1802122094 Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network in 
Serbo-Croatian 1100 GMT 18 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU1802122094 </F>
<F P=104>  Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Serbo-Croatian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Mirza Sadikovic from Bihac] </F>
  [Text] The Serbian aggressor has continued the 
artillery-tank attacks on the defense lines running from the 
Grmusko-Srbljanski plateau, via Vasino Brdo, to the army 
barracks in Grabez. 
  In the course of the night and this morning they attempted 
new infantry breakthroughs, which our defenders thwarted 
heroically. 
  [Word indistinct] in the course of the night the intensity 
of 
the shelling [words indistinct] was reduced somewhat. It has 
been intensified this morning, especially at the time that we 
are reporting this. 
  After a tenacious counterattack by the members of the 5th 
Corps against the remainder of the para-army [words indistinct] 
a new break and end of hostilities. [Words indistinct] 
separating lines in this period was a little more peaceful. 
  Yesterday's [words indistinct] Bosanska Krupa. In front and 
[word indistinct] international community [words indistinct]. 

