<F P=103> LD1702221394 </F>
<F P=104>  Zagreb Radio Croatia Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Serbo-Croatian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The newly elected president of the presidential 
council of the Croat Republic of Herzeg-Bosna, Kresimir Zubak, 
will head the Bosnian Croat delegation in the next round of 
Geneva talks early next month. Members of the negotiating 
delegation will be elected by the Chamber of Deputies or some 
other body in the Croat Republic of Herzeg-Bosna. 
  The newly elected president of the Presidential Council of 
Herzeg-Bosna informed the deputies about the current situation 
at the Geneva peace negotiations. He said that certain new 
initiatives on the set-up of Bosnia-Herzegovina had been 
presented in Geneva, but added that it was too early to discuss 
them. However, the new initiatives refer to the involvement of 
the United States into the solving of the crisis in 
Bosnia-Herzegovina and to NATO's decision to bomb Serb positions 
around Sarajevo if the Serbs do not withdraw their weapons. 

