<F P=100> BOSNIA-HERZEGOVINA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Croat Assembly Declares Unilateral Cease-Fire </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1702214194 Zagreb Radio Croatia Network in Serbo-Croatian 
2100 GMT 17 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1702214194 </F>
<F P=104>  Zagreb Radio Croatia Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Serbo-Croatian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpts] At the end of its session in Mostar this 
evening, the Chamber of Deputies of the Croat republic of 
Herceg-Bosna passed a decision on a unilateral cease-fire and 
truce in Mostar for the next 15 days. [passage omitted] 
  At the proposal of Defense Minister Perica Jukic, the 
Chamber 
of Deputies passed a decision on a unilateral cease-fire and 
truce in the Mostar area for a period of 15 days. The 
Presidential Council, the Defense Ministry, and the HVO 
[Croatian Defense Council] main headquarters were charged with 
implementing this decision, which specifies that the HVO is 
allowed to open fire only in self defense. 
  The Chamber of Deputies also passed a decision to open an 
office of the Croat republic of Herceg-Bosna to take care of all 
issues relating to the rights and status of Croats. The office 
will be located in Pale and also in Banja Luka, Tuzla, and 
Sarajevo. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

