<F P=100> BULGARIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Foreign Ministry Declaration on Serb Withdrawal </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU2102144094 Sofia Khorizont Radio Network in Bulgarian 1400 
GMT 21 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU2102144094 </F>
<F P=104>  Sofia Khorizont Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Bulgarian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] A declaration of the Bulgarian Ministry of Foreign 
Affairs describes the process of withdrawing heavy armaments 
from Sarajevo as a sign of hope in connection with halting the 
military operations and in connection with solving the problems 
at the negotiating table. 
  The document expresses high appreciation for the efforts of 
the United Nations, NATO, the United States, and Russia, which 
although somewhat belated have demonstrated that acceptable 
solutions to alleviate the conflict can be achieved on the basis 
of coordinated efforts. 
  As a country closely situated near the area of the conflict 
and bearing a heavy share of the burden imposed by the 
international sanctions, the Republic of Bulgaria has a vital 
interest in promptly finding a just and lasting solution of the 
conflict, the declaration further reads. 
  The declaration points out that in confirming its resolve of 
not interfering in the armed conflict, the Republic of Bulgaria 
once again expresses its readiness to support all international 
efforts aimed at a peaceful and just solution of the conflict on 
the territory of former Yugoslavia. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

