<F P=100> HUNGARY </F>
<H3> <TI>   Discusses Economy, Bosnia </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2002112494 Budapest Kossuth Radio Network in Hungarian 
1000 GMT 20 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2002112494 </F>
<F P=104>  Budapest Kossuth Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Hungarian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Lajos Fur, the new chairman of the MDF [Hungarian 
Democratic Forum], has pledged to continue the policy of Joszef 
Antall. In the Sunday Newspaper radio program, he stressed that 
there must be reconciliation between the churches and various 
strata of society. 
  Evaluating the government party's economic policy, Fur said 
that it has been possible to squeeze back inflation. He 
mentioned by way of example that in January price increases were 
barely above 3 percent, although they had themselves been 
reckoning with inflation of around 6 percent. Economic growth 
had already begun last year, he said, mentioning the building 
industry as an example. 
  Lajos Fur spoke about the situation that has evolved along 
our southern borders. The Hungarian Government's position is 
unequivocal: It does not wish to get mixed up in the conflict 
and it also declared that when it stated that in the event of 
conflict, NATO planes would not be allowed into Hungary's 
airspace. The MDF chairman is of the view that there will 
probably not be any need for NATO air strikes, because the 
warring sides in Bosnia will hopefully see reason. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

