<F P=100> HUNGARY </F>
<H3> <TI>   Prime Minister Addresses MDF Convention </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2002184294 Budapest Kossuth Radio Network in Hungarian 
1600 GMT 20 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2002184294 </F>
<F P=104>  Budapest Kossuth Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Hungarian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] According to Hungarian Prime Minister Peter Boross, 
a democratic state that rejects both totalitarianism and 
excessive liberalism has to be established in Hungary. In his 
closing address to the National Convention of the Hungarian 
Democratic Forum [MDF] Boross said that legislation should 
continue to be given a dominant role in the future. However, 
the executive power should also be given adequate scope. 
  According to Boross, there is a need for a foreign policy 
which keeps in view the integration into the West as well as the 
life of Hungarians beyond the borders. The prime minister also 
spoke about the responsibility of the media, saying that the 
country needed objective, nonparty political, but pronation 
[nemzeti] public service media. 

</TEXT>

