<F P=100> CZECH REPUBLIC </F>
<H3> <TI>   Foreign Ministry Disagrees With Baudys's Initiative </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2102135894 Prague Radiozurnal Radio Network in Czech 1300 
GMT 21 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2102135894 </F>
<F P=104>  Prague Radiozurnal Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Czech </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The Czech Foreign Ministry today expressed 
fundamental disagreement with the action of Defense Minister 
Antonin Baudys, who, at the end of last week, submitted to some 
foreign representatives his initiative for solving the situation 
in Bosnia. 
  According to the Foreign Ministry's statement, the action of 
[Defense] Minister [Antonin] Baudys has created a totally 
unacceptable situation for the foreign policy interests of the 
Czech Republic, has damaged its reputation, and is a clear 
infringement of a government minister's jurisdiction. 

</TEXT>

