<F P=100> CZECH REPUBLIC </F>
<H3> <TI>   Presentation of Initiative `Unusual' </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2102215394 Prague Radiozurnal Radio Network in Czech 2000 
GMT 21 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2102215394 </F>
<F P=104>  Prague Radiozurnal Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Czech </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] In an interview with journalists during his visit to 
Turkey, Defense Minister Antonin Baudys admitted today that the 
way his initiative was made public, without preliminary 
consultation with the government, was unusual. He said that he 
had been forced to take this course of action by the approaching 
deadline of the NATO ultimatum to Bosnia Serbs. He said that 
his intention was guided by a wish that several ideas were 
tabled to the international officials who could make a decision 
on the issues concerned. 
  According to Baudys, a possible lengthy debate on the 
initiative in Czech political structures would have devalued the 
content of the document. 

</TEXT>

