<H3> <TI>   HVO-Bosnian Talks Postponed </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2202131194 Zagreb Radio Croatia Network in Serbo-Croatian 
1200 GMT 22 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2202131194 </F>
<F P=104>  Zagreb Radio Croatia Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Serbo-Croatian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] According to the Public Relations Office of the 
UNPROFOR Command in Zagreb, today's scheduled meeting between 
the Croat Defense Council [HVO] Commander, General Ante Roso, 
and the commander of the Bosnia-Herzegovina Army, General Rasim 
Delic will not take place. A spokesman for UNPROFOR could not 
reveal the reasons behind the postponement of their meeting. 
  Croatian sources assume that Gen Delic has encountered some 
difficulties while on his way to Zagreb. The talks between 
generals Delic and Roso were arranged during a recent round of 
the Geneva negotiations between Croat Minister for Foreign 
Affairs Mate Granic and Bosnia-Herzegovina Prime minister Haris 
Silajdzic. They reconfirmed this arrangement when they met in 
Frankfurt last Saturday. 
  Yesterday, following their meeting with UN Secretary General 
Butrus-Ghali's special envoy Yasushi Akashi at the UNPROFOR 
Headquarters in Zagreb, HVO generals Ante Roso and Milivoj 
Petkovic said that they would hold talks today with Rasim Delic 
and that they hoped they would sign an agreement on the 
cessation of hostilities. 
  Speaking about the possibilities of signing an agreement on 
the cessation of hostilites, Akashi yesterday said that this 
would be an historic moment in the return of peace to 
Bosnia-Herzegovina. 

</TEXT>

