<F P=100> CROATIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   RSK President Appoints New Army Chief </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2202160594 Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service in 
Serbo-Croatian 1527 GMT 22 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2202160594 </F>
<F P=104>  Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Serbo-Croatian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Knin, 22 Feb (TANJUG) -- Milan Martic, the president 
of the republic of Serb Krajina [RSK], has -- on the basis of 
his constitutional and legal powers -- relieved Major General 
Mile Novakovic, the hitherto chief of general staff of the RSK 
army, of his duty, ISKRA [Krajina news agency] has learned from 
the office of the president of the republic. 
  Major General Milan Celeketic has been appointed new chief 
of 
the general staff of the RSK army. 
  Celeketic was born in 1946 in Mokrin, the municipality of 
Kikinda, [Vojvodina, Serbia]. He graduated from the military 
academy and other military schools. 
  He has held a number of responsible posts in the RSK army 
since the very beginning of the Croatian-Krajina conflict when 
he unreservedly sided with the Serbian people. 
  He has participated in all the major combat operations in 
western Slavonia and Posavina. 
  In the course of fighting for the corridor [northern Bosnia] 
he contributed a great deal to the battles for the liberation of 
Derventa and Bosanski Brod. 
  Prior to his appointment General Celeketic was in command of 
the famed RSK army 18th corps. The RSK army commander has been 
decorated with high military awards for his work. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

