<F P=102>  LD2202121094 Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service in 
Serbo-Croatian 1103 GMT 22 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2202121094 </F>
<F P=104>  Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Serbo-Croatian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpt] Zvornik, 22 Feb (TANJUG) -- The Muslim side again 
violated the cease-fire last night in the Sarajevo area, TANJUG 
learned from Serb military sources in the Srpska republic. 
  According to the same sources, UNPROFOR [UN Protection 
Forces] members identified the culprits and the location from 
which they opened fire, and "a resolute effort" was made to stop 
the shooting from Muslim positions. 
  According to Serb military sources, members of Muslim units 
have been using infantry weapons to target Serb areas from 
several directions. The Muslim side violated the cease-fire in 
the Lukavica, Lemezovic Kuca, Kosevo, and Grbavica areas of 
Sarajevo. [passage omitted] 

