<F P=102>  LD1902174494 Zagreb Radio Croatia Network in Serbo-Croatian 
1700 GMT 19 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1902174494 </F>
<F P=104>  Zagreb Radio Croatia Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Serbo-Croatian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Correspondent Ivica Saric reporting for Croatian Radio from </F>
Vitez] 
  [Excerpt] According to the HVO's [Croatian Defense Council] 
operational zone in Vitez [largest Croat enclave in central 
Bosnia], the town center came under an artillery attack again 
last night. Two civilians were wounded. 
  According to the same source, the Muslim Army is deploying 
fresh units on the northern approaches to Vitez. The command of 
the Vitez operational zone links this with the lifting of the 
blockade of Sarajevo and a large influx of infantry belonging to 
the Muslim Army's First Corps [based in Sarajevo] to Croat areas 
in central Bosnia. [passage omitted] 

