<H3> <TI>   Croats Protest Muslim Infantry Movement </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2102194594 Zagreb HTV Television in Serbo-Croatian 1830 
GMT 21 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2102194594 </F>
<F P=104>  Zagreb HTV Television </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Serbo-Croatian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Mayors of [the Croat-held towns of] Kresevo, 
Kiseljak, and Fojnica today sent a [joint] letter to the 
UNPROFOR [UN Protection Forces] command. In the letter they are 
asking whether UNPROFOR is going to do anything to prevent 
Muslim infantry units, currently being moved from Sarajevo, from 
taking part in the offensive against the Croat areas in central 
Bosnia. 
  The Muslim infantry is no longer needed in Sarajevo and they 
are already moving into central Bosnia, with the aim of 
occupying Croat areas, the letter says. 

