<H3> <TI>   Civilian Targets Shelled in Maglaj </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU2102171494 Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network in 
Serbo-Croatian 1400 GMT 21 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU2102171494 </F>
<F P=104>  Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Serbo-Croatian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Hajrudin Sermic from Maglaj] </F>
  [Text] Maglaj is today again the target of the aggressor's 
artillery weapons. The criminals continue to employ their 
surprise tactic of sudden shelling, usually at times when the 
population is most relaxed. Their sole objective is to kill as 
many innocent people as possible. A general alarm signal was 
sounded at 1300 [1200 GMT] because some 10 120-mm mortar shells 
were launched at the town center in a relatively short period. 
The shelling of civilian targets is still in progress. We do 
not have any information on the killed and wounded, but we do 
know for certain that there are casualties. 

</TEXT>

