<F P=100> ROMANIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Coposu Reviews European Tour, Visit With King </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU2102174594 Bucharest Radio Romania Network in Romanian 
1400 GMT 21 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU2102174594 </F>
<F P=104>  Bucharest Radio Romania Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Romanian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] At a news conference today, Corneliu Coposu, 
chairman of the National Peasant Christian-Democratic Party 
[PNTCD], discussed the results of his recent tour through a 
number of European countries. Coposu said that, generally 
speaking, Romania enjoys the sympathy of the West, but there is 
also some reticence, which Coposu termed as a tendency to set up 
a left-wing government and reestablish communism in Romania. As 
a consequence of this, Coposu stressed that the West might 
reconsider its position regarding Romania's final acceptance as 
a full member of the Council of Europe. 
  Coposu also said that during his tour, he paid a visit to 
Versoix [Switzerland, residence of Romanian King], where he met 
with the former sovereign of Romania, after which he emphasized 
that the king does not intend to apply for an entry visa for 
Easter or 10 May [Romania's national day during the monarchy], 
although he did express his wish to visit Romania as soon as 
possible, reports our correspondent Iulia Gherman. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

