<F P=100> ROMANIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Senate Panel To Investigate </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU2202093594 Bucharest Radio Romania Network in Romanian 
1400 GMT 21 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU2202093594 </F>
<F P=104>  Bucharest Radio Romania Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Romanian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Shortly after 1500 the Senate resumed its plenary 
session in Omnia Hall. After the agenda was agreed, they 
discussed a number of organizational issues. 
  Following this, the chairman of the session, Senate Speaker 
Oliviu Gherman presented a communique released by the Senate 
Commission for Defense, Public Order, and National Security 
referring to the accusations of [Greater Romania Party] Senator 
Corneliu Vadim Tudor made during the plenary session of the 
Senate and by means of the mass media against the minister of 
national defense [Lieutenant General Nicolae Spiroiu] and other 
top officials in that ministry. The communique states that, 
quote, within the next two weeks the commission will examine the 
documents and the assertions underlying those accusations, as 
well as the extent to which the comply with reality. On the 
basis of the conclusions that will be drawn from those 
investigations the Commission for Defense, Public Order, and 
National Security will make suggestions to the Senate with 
respect to the way in which the case should be solved, unquote. 
  Our correspondent, Victor Spirache, reports that the session 
then proceeded to hear a number of reports elaborated by the 
mediation commissions [mediating between the Senate and the 
Chamber of Deputies], after which the senators continued to 
discuss the articles of the draft bill on labor protection. 

</TEXT>

