<F P=100> SLOVAKIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   SDL Chairman Rejects Accusation </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1802174794 Bratislava Rozhlasova Stanica Slovensko Network 
in Slovak 1600 GMT 18 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1802174794 </F>
<F P=104>  Bratislava Rozhlasova Stanica Slovensko Network 
in Slovak 1600 GMT 18 Feb 94 </F>



<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105>Slovak </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] At a special news conference held in the 
parliamentary building today, Peter Weiss, chairman of the Party 
of the Democratic Left [SDL], rejected accusations levelled 
against the SDL that they had attempted to blackmail Prime 
Minister Meciar and the Movement for a Democratic Slovakia 
[HZDS]. Weiss said that on the basis of the 17 February debate 
on the endorsement of privatization projects, Deputy Juraj 
Plesnik, as the vice chairman of the parliamentary committee for 
privatization, had examined certain procedures adopted by the 
government when endorsing privatization projects during the past 
days. He had come to a conclusion that a suspicion existed that 
the law had been violated. 
  Weiss went on to say that, in view of the seriousness of the 
content of the speech Deputy Plesnik had planned to make to the 
National Council, he had deemed it appropriate to inform 
parliamentary speaker Ivan Gasparovic. The latter had visited 
Vladimir Meciar and had given him the first version of the draft 
resolution. According to Weiss, that version had been different 
than the one Deputy Plesnik had delivered to the National 
Council. 
  Weiss regards the move made by Meciar as being a pretext to 
prevent an agreement on holding an early election and a 
referendum. 

</TEXT>

