<H3> <TI>   Slota Says Party `Purified' </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1902221494 Bratislava STV 1 Television Network in Slovak 
1830 GMT 19 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1902221494 </F>
<F P=104>  Bratislava STV 1 Television Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Slovak </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The Slovak National Party [SNS] has been purified 
after the departure of Cernak and his colleagues. In the 
future, it will again have a national orientation, as its name 
indicates. 
  Jan Slota said this at a briefing in Zilina after his being 
elected chairman of the SNS. 
  According to Slota, the SNS will continue to cooperate with 
the Movement for a Democratic Slovakia as a coalition partner, 
while supporting programs of other parties that have the good of 
Slovak citizens in mind. 

</TEXT>

