<F P=100> SLOVAKIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Cernak's Group To Establish New Party </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2102174794 Bratislava Rozhlasova Stanica Slovensko Network 
in Slovak 1100 GMT 21 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2102174794 </F>
<F P=104>  Bratislava Rozhlasova Stanica Slovensko Network 
in Slovak 1100 GMT 21 Feb 94 </F>



<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105>Slovak </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpts] Members of the parliamentary National Democratic 
Club of the Slovak National Party [SNS] headed by Ludovit Cernak 
have decided to establish a new party with the working title 
National Democratic Party [Narodno Demokraticka Strana]. In 
this context our correspondent asked the leader of this group 
Ludovit Cernak for a comment. [passage omitted] 
  [Correspondent] How will the situation that has arisen 
affect 
the Slovak domestic political scene as a whole? 
  [Cernak] It will affect the domestic political situation. We 
have to find a proper place, a place we belong to. We will have 
to do this, so that a normal voter would recognize whose 
policies are demagogic and who is genuinely interested in 
defending Slovakia's interests. In the medium term, given the 
people we have, given their ideas and their potential, I dare 
say I will very quickly build a nationally oriented alternative 
for Slovakia, an alternative that will not play second fiddle in 
the early parliamentary elections. 
  [Correspondent] In what way are you going to sort out the 
situation of the SNS National Democratic group in the parliament? 
  [Cernak] It is likely that the decision to expel us and to 
urge us to surrender our mandates will not be made in the 
parliament. But no matter what happens, we will retain our 
membership in the deputies' group we have created and we will be 
implementing the policy which the whole group and not only our 
faction should have represented. We will give the correct names 
to all the deeds and all the mishaps, so that the Slovak voter 
will not succumb to populism again, so that this voter can 
compare words with deeds. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

