<H3> <TI>   Greece Closes Border; Consul Leaves Skopje </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2002162994 Zagreb Radio Croatia Network in Serbo-Croatian 
1500 GMT 20 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2002162994 </F>
<F P=104>  Zagreb Radio Croatia Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Serbo-Croatian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The Greek Consul to Macedonia [Former Yugoslav 
Republic of Macedonia -- FYROM] Elias Eliadis today officially 
left Macedonia. The complete furnishings from the Skopje-based 
consulate were also moved to Greece. 
  Border crossings on the Greek-Macedonian border will be 
closed until further notice, not only for Macedonian citizens 
and vehicles, but also for citizens from European countries, 
with the exception of the citizens of the Federal Republic of 
Yugoslavia. As Macedonian radio has reported, long lines of 
heavy vehicles from Italy, the Netherlands, Denmark, Germany, 
Macedonia, and other countries are piling up on both sides of 
the border. Rail traffic was also interrupted in recent days. 

</TEXT>

