<F P=102>  AU2202112494 Skopje MIC in English 21 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU2202112494 </F>
<F P=104>  Skopje MIC </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Unattributed report: "FRY Discreetly Supports Greek </F>
Blockade"] 
  [Text] The economic sanctions of Greece against Macedonia 
[The Former Yugoslav Republic of Macedonia -- FYROM] still 
remains without any public reactions from official Belgrade. 
The exception is only the party SK-DJ [Communist League 
Movement for Yugoslavia], which condemned this uncivilized Greek 
act, and emphasized that the consequences would mostly be felt 
by the innocent citizens. 
  However, the most obvious demonstration of the policy of 
double standards is best represented by the attitude of the FRY 
[Federal Republic of Yugoslavia], which, at a state level, came 
out against the UN intention to impose sanctions against 
Croatia, while it silently supported an illegal and damaging 
Greek measure, otherwise, immediately condemned throughout the 
world. 

