<F P=102>  LD2102174694 Warsaw Radio Warszawa Network in Polish 1500 
GMT 21 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2102174694 </F>
<F P=104>  Warsaw Radio Warszawa Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Polish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The Swiss Foreign Minister Flavio Cotti, who is now 
in Poland, and Foreign Minister Andrzej Olechowski have 
announced that President Lech Walesa would be paying a three-day 
visit to the Swiss Confederation in the second half of May. 
  Much attention was paid during talks to the possibilities of 
improving economic cooperation between our two countries. 
Attention was also drawn to the need to build a security system 
in this part of Europe. 
  Andrzej Olechowski assessed relations between Poland and 
Switzerland very positively. 
  [Begin Olechowski recording] It is a country whose 
friendship 
and will to help and cooperate with Poland is something we 
experience every day. Today too this willingness was expressed 
both in the interest shown by the minister in events in our 
region, in his understanding of the importance of this region 
for the future of Europe and in his understanding -- which we 
traditionally find among the Swiss -- for economic affairs, 
something which we also discussed for quite a while. 

