<F P=100> POLAND </F>
<H3> <TI>   Longest Postwar Miners Strike Ends </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1902174894 Warsaw TV Polonia Network in Polish 1600 GMT 19 
Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1902174894 </F>
<F P=104>  Warsaw TV Polonia Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Polish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The longest strike in the post-war history of Poland 
ended last night. After 19 days, 78 miners from the Pomorzany 
mine [belonging to the Boleslaw Mining and Metallurgical Plant] 
returned to the surface. 
  A signed agreement guarantees the miners a pay rise of 1.5 
million zlotys a month and a quarterly bonus based on the 
enterprise's profits. According to the director of the Boleslaw 
mining and metallurgical plant this is all the enterprise can 
manage at the moment. 

</TEXT>

