<F P=100> POLAND </F>
<H3> <TI>   Ministry Supports NATO Position on Bosnia </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2102135494 Warsaw Radio Warszawa Network in Polish 1300 
GMT 21 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2102135494 </F>
<F P=104>  Warsaw Radio Warszawa Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Polish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The Polish Ministry of Foreign Affairs [MSZ] fully 
supports the position of the NATO states with regard to military 
intervention in the conflict in Bosnia-Herzegovina. According 
to Jerzy Chmielewski, of the MSZ European Department, the 
current situation, which has arisen after the expiry of the NATO 
ultimatum to the Bosnian Serbs, should be used to consolidate 
the ceasefire and resume peace talks between the parties 
involved. Chmielewski's opinion is that as a transition stage, 
new areas in Bosnia-Herzegovina could be incorporated into the 
security zones. 

</TEXT>

