<F P=101> Albania </F>
<H3> <TI>   Macedonian Foreign Minister Crvenkovski Visits </TI></H3>
<H4>   Agrees To Expand Relations </H4>
<F P=102> AU1902175394 Tirana ATA in English 1123 GMT 19 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU1902175394 </F>
<F P=104>  Tirana ATA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Tirana, February 19 (ATA) -- The foreign ministers 
of Albania and FYROM [The Former Yugoslav Republic of 
Macedonia], Mr. Alfred Serreqi and Mr. Stevo Crvenkovski met 
yesterday before noon in Tirana and expressed their will for the 
further deepening of the relations between the two countries. 
They agreed to extend the diplomatic relations and to create a 
join governmental commission for the intensification of the 
economical cooperation between Albania and FYROM. 
  The chiefs of the diplomacy of the two countries both 
accepted the lifting of the visas and the tax customs in the 
border. They both expressed their will for the accelerating of 
carrying out the project for the speedway east-west, which will 
connect Durres, Skopje, Sofia and Istanbul. 
  Ministers Serreqi and Crvenkovski agreed to extend 
cooperation especially in the fields of culture and energy and 
spoke about the possibility to carry out a railway which will 
connect both countries. 
  The Albanian side asked for the census of population in the 
former Yugoslav Republic of Macedonia to be done under the 
control of the international observers. 
  The ministers talked also about the tense situation in the 
region. 

</TEXT>

