Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Tirana, February 19 (ATA) -- The chairman of the 
parliamentary Commission for the Foreign Policy, Mr. Eduard 
Selami, received yesterday the foreign minister of FYROM [The 
Former Yugoslav Republic of Macedonia], Mr. Stevo Crvenkovski. 
  During the meeting, both persons exchanged opinions about 
the 
development of the bilateral relations in the political and 
economical fields. "The Republic of Macedonia as well as the 
Republic of Albania is experiencing today great political 
changes and especially economical changes, said Mr. Crvenkovski. 
This calls for a closer cooperation between the two countries 
in this fields, which will serve to the aim of having the same 
approach in the international arena." 
  Mr. Selami said that Albania also is interested on the 
strengthening of the bilateral relations, which serves both our 
countries and the peace in the Balkan region. He repeated once 
more the request for the guarantee of the rights of the 
Albanians in Macedonia, rights which are recognized from the 
international documents. 

