<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpts] Prague Feb 22 (CTK) -- The leadership of the 
Christian Democratic Union-Czechoslovak People's Party (KDU-CSL) 
appreciated the ethical aspect of Defence Minister Antonin 
Baudys's appeal and did not ask him to resign from his post, 
Baudys himself told journalists after the session of the party 
leadership. [passage omitted] 
  "The leadership has supported in a way the ethical aspect of 
the call," said Baudys, adding that the dismissal of a minister 
should be preceded by the talks of the coalition parties about 
this move. The ethical aspect of his appeal should not be 
suppressed by formal shortcomings, he said. 
  The KDU-CSL meeting was not attended by Josef Lux, the party 
chairman. 
  On Monday [21 February] the Executive Council of the Civic 
Democratic Party (ODS, the largest coalition party), recommended 
to Premier Vaclav Klaus that he take strict measures, perhaps 
even Baudys's dismissal. 

