<H3> <TI>   Russia's Kozyrev Arrives for Talks </TI></H3>
<H4>   Meets With Goncz </H4>
<F P=102> AU2202145594 Budapest MTI in English 1420 GMT 22 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU2202145594 </F>
<F P=104>  Budapest MTI </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Budapest, 22 February (MTI) -- Hungarian President 
Arpad Goncz met with Russian Foreign Minister Andrei Kozyrev in 
the Parliament today. 
  Presidential spokesman Andras Farago said the president 
congratulated Kozyrev on the joint Russian-Western success in 
dealing with the the situation in Sarajevo. 
  In Hungary's view, NATO's Partnership for Peace is not an 
empty initiative but a practicable scheme giving attention to 
the human, legal, and social factors of security, in addition to 
its military side. 
  Kozyrev conveyed greetings from President Boris Yeltsin to 
Goncz. He assured Goncz that Moscow always examines how its 
foreign policy moves contribute to Central-European stability. 
  He said Moscow supports cooperation and peace partnership 
with NATO, but stressed the need to find concrete solutions to 
individual problems in the region. 
  Russia also attaches great importance to the CSCE and its 
summit, to be held in Budapest at the end of the year. 

</TEXT>

