<H3> <TI>   Russia's Kozyrev Arrives for Talks </TI></H3>
<H4>   Holds Talks With Boross </H4>
<F P=102> AU2202182394 Budapest MTI in English 1443 GMT 22 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU2202182394 </F>
<F P=104>  Budapest MTI </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Budapest, 22 February (MTI) -- Hungarian Prime 
Minister Peter Boross met with Russian Foreign Minister Andrei 
Kozyrev in the Parliament on Tuesday [22 February]. 
  According to foreign affairs spokesman Janos Herman, Boross 
told Kozyrev that Budapest looks forward to the visit of Russian 
Prime Minister Viktor Chernomyrdin. 
  Regarding the south Slav crisis, Boross stressed Hungary is 
glad that the planned military intervention in Bosnia had become 
unnecessary, and recognizes the role Russia played in this. 
  Kozyrev expressed the hope that Russia and Hungary would 
soon 
work out a number of agreements giving business links a new 
impetus. Recent positive movement in bilateral economic ties 
provides a good basis for Chernomyrdin's trip to Hungary, he 
added. 
  The Russian foreign minister sees good chances for 
ratification of the Hungarian-Russian basic treaty, which 
complies with Russian interests. 
  Kozyrev concluded his two-day state visit to Hungary and 
left 
Budapest today. 

</TEXT>

