<F P=101> Hungary </F>
<H3> <TI>   Military Cooperation Accord Signed With Italy </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU2202181994 Budapest MTI in English 1646 GMT 22 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU2202181994 </F>
<F P=104>  Budapest MTI </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Budapest, 22 February (MTI) -- Ministers of Defense 
Lajos Fur of Hungary and Fabio Fabbri of Italy signed a 
cooperation agreement between the armed forces of the two 
countries, in Budapest on Tuesday [22 February]. 
  The ministers also held talks on the possibilities of joint 
military exercises. 
  At a press conference following the signing, Fabio Fabbri 
said Rome welcomed the American proposal of peace-partnership. 
The signed Hungarian-Italian agreement relates to this, 
extending to mutual training of officers, constant military 
consultations, and cooperation between the military industries 
of the two countries. 
  The agreement also covers an already existing cooperation 
between the military secret services. 
  The Italian minister, who arrived in Budapest on Tuesday, 
also raised the possibility of joint Hungarian-Italian military 
exercises, the implementation of which are being examined. 
  Minister Fur agreed with examining the opportunities for 
joint military exercises, the dates for these being dependent on 
NATO relations development. 

</TEXT>

