<H3> <TI>   Vacaroiu, Polish Minister Discuss Cooperation </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU2202181694 Bucharest ROMPRES in English 1550 GMT 22 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU2202181694 </F>
<F P=104>  Bucharest ROMPRES </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Bucharest, ROMPRES 22/2/1994 -- "Together, we can 
surpass many problems," said Romanian Prime Minister Nicolae 
Vacaroiu during his interview on Tuesday with Poland's Defense 
Minister Piotr Kolodziejczyk. 
  The Polish dignitary is visiting Bucharest in order to sign 
a 
military cooperation agreement expected to induce tighter 
bilateral relations in all fields. The collocutors expressed 
their desire to develop the bilateral economic relations, 
according to the real potential of the two economies. 
  The cooperation between traditional friends, such as Romania 
and Poland, based on updated, flexible and pragmatical 
agreements, are contributing to the building up of a stable 
structure on the continent, was a conclusion of the interview, 
attended also by Romanian Defense Minister Lieutenant-General 
Niculae Spiroiu and by Polish ambassador in Bucharest. 
  Premier Vacaroiu requested that the desire for intensified 
bilateral contacts be conveyed to his Polish counterpart. 
  The talks occasioned also an exchange of opinions on the 
"Partnership for Peace" recently joined in both by Romania and 
Poland. 

