<F P=100> ROMANIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Union Leader Pins Hopes on Commission Inquiry </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU2002144094 Bucharest Radio Romania Network in Romanian 
1100 GMT 20 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU2002144094 </F>
<F P=104>  Bucharest Radio Romania Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Romanian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] On his return to Targu Jiu, Nicolae Mihu, leader of 
the Lignitul Mining Trade Union Federation, told our 
correspondent Titus Stoichitoiu that he is totally disappointed 
with the negotiations that were conducted in Bucharest last 
Friday and Saturday [18-19 February]. In spite of all that, he 
is optimistically looking forward to the arrival in Gorj County 
tomorrow of the governmental inquiry commission scheduled to 
investigate irregularities in the activity of the Brown Coal 
Public Corporation, which might lead to the strike being ended. 
Otherwise, Mr. Nicolae Mihu said, the coordinating council of 
the Lignitul Mining Trade Union Federation intends to continue 
the strike action in the mining units and to explain to the 
miners that they should no longer go to Targu Jiu, as Miron 
Cosma demanded from them last Friday night. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

